==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nopal
<hw>No"pal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Mexican
<ets>nopalli</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A cactaceous plant
(<spn>Nopalea cochinellifera</spn>), originally Mexican, on which the
cochineal insect feeds, and from which it is collected. The name is
sometimes given to other species of <gen>Cactaceae</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

